Vanessa Jones' oldest child was regularly falling asleep to the television, and her youngest begged to go to Dairy Queen to get a toy advertised on TV. She and her friends are increasingly concerned about children's television -- the commercials, the programming and the fact that kids are just sitting there instead of playing. High-profile reports have linked television watching to childhood obesity, for example. That has left children's networks -- including the No. 2 player -- Cartoon Network -- with a tricky balancing act. 